modules.description: Pings an InfluxDB host and writes a list of data points with specified precision and connection parameters. Operates on strings, integers, and Influxdb.Point.t structures. Used to monitor server availability and submit time-series data asynchronously.

Handles asynchronous communication with InfluxDB, offering write and query operations for time-series data. It works with data structures such as point records, query strings, and response parsers. Used to stream sensor data into InfluxDB and retrieve historical metrics for analysis.

Provides asynchronous interaction with InfluxDB by pinging hosts and writing time-series data. Processes strings, integers, and point structures with precision and connection settings. Enables monitoring server status and submitting data without blocking execution. Supports scenarios like real-time metrics collection and health checks.
